                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-28T11:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28</hi>[<hi rend="italic">29?</hi>], <hi
                                rend="italic">1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 29—4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Am orally informed by Foreign Office that Council of Ministers has approved
                    prolongation of commercial <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> with the United
                    States until April 10, 1929, according to existing provisions of law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
